  "texts": [
    "In HCAI, XAI is crucial as it aids in building trust and confidence in AI systems and ensures that users can understand, verify, and challenge AI outcomes.",
    "Furthermore, XAI can help in guaranteeing accountability in case of incidents.While HCI is concerned with the interaction with user interfaces and AI is concerned with creating models that impart intelligence to the application, the creation of systems that can be used outside of experimental settings falls into the area of Software Engineering (SE).",
    "In the context of HCAI, SE enables the creation of quality systems, ensuring that AI systems are designed, developed, and maintained efficiently and effectively [14].",
    "SE practices are also crucial for integrating AI systems into larger software systems, ensuring reliability, scalability, and maintainability while guaranteeing human-centered design principles.",
    "A subfield of HCI that overlaps with SE is End-User Development (EUD)."
  ],
